block.p: Corinne Linda Finegan and Jens Reinhold Machatzke were married yesterday by the Rev. Leslie C. Smith at Trinity Episcopal Church in Princeton, N.J.

Ms. Finegan, 33, is keeping her name. She is the senior director of the photo product group of Excite@Home, the Internet company in Redwood City, Calif. She graduated magna cum laude from Tufts University and received an M.B.A. from Stanford. She is a daughter of Patricia McKee Finegan and Paul J. Finegan of Hopewell Township, N.J. Her mother is the nurse at Morgan Elementary School in Hamilton, N.J. Her father is a stock trader and a member of the American Stock Exchange in New York.
Corinne Linda Finegan and Jens Reinhold Machatzke were married yesterday by the Rev. Leslie C. Smith at Trinity Episcopal Church in Princeton, N.J.

Ms. Finegan, 33, is keeping her name. She is the senior director of the photo product group of Excite@Home, the Internet company in Redwood City, Calif. She graduated magna cum laude from Tufts University and received an M.B.A. from Stanford. She is a daughter of Patricia McKee Finegan and Paul J. Finegan of Hopewell Township, N.J. Her mother is the nurse at Morgan Elementary School in Hamilton, N.J. Her father is a stock trader and a member of the American Stock Exchange in New York.

Mr. Machatzke, 34, is the director of customer operations at Equinix, a telecommunications company in Redwood City. He received bachelor's and master's degrees in engineering from Stanford and an M.B.A. from Harvard. He is a son of Traudel I. Machatzke and Dr. Heinz W. Machatzke of Sewickley Heights, Pa. His father is the dean of the Bayer School of Natural and Environmental Sciences at Duquesne University in Pittsburgh.
